{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014bn1KoNXpRWv1o34cKHqiK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The test is failing because Change 4 (section label join relaxation) now generates the 2-line join \"INGREDIENTS MOZZARELLA STICKS\":\n- \"INGREDIENTS\" is a section label\n- \"INGREDIENTS MOZZARELLA STICKS\" has 3 words > 2, so NOT blocked\n\nThe test input is: `\"INGREDIENTS\\nMOZZARELLA STICKS\\n- 2 tbsp sugar\"`\n\nWith the new join logic:\n- `isSectionLabel(\"INGREDIENTS\") && wordCount(\"INGREDIENTS MOZZARELLA STICKS\") <= 2`\n- = `true && 3 <= 2` = false → NOT blocked → join generated\n\n\nThe real issue is that instruction section labels like \"INGREDIENTS\" and \"DIRECTIONS\" should never join with following lines, but the relaxation was meant to allow category labels like \"Zupy\" to legitimately start a title. I need to distinguish between these two types of labels instead of applying the word count check uniformly. still blocked. `Zupy` followed by `Zimowe` + `Warzywne` produces `Zupy Zimowe Warzywne` (3 words) — allowed.\n\nBut the issue is that \"INGREDIENTS MOZZARELLA STICKS\" is also 3 words. The fix needs to be more targeted.\n\nLooking at the SECTION_LABELS set, there are two types:\n1. Recipe section labels: \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", etc. - these should ALWAYS block joins\n2. Category labels: \"zupy\", \"placki\", \"warzywa\", etc. - these should allow joins when total words >= 3\n\nThe improvement plan's Change 4 is specifically about \"Zupy\" (a category label) being in SECTION_LABELS. The fix should only relax the block for category-type labels, not for recipe-internal section labels like \"ingredients\".\n\nI need to distinguish between recipe-internal labels that should always block joins and category labels that can participate in joins when the result reaches 3 words. The recipe-internal ones — ingredients, directions, instructions, method, preparation, steps, notes, tip, tips, variations, variation, garn — should remain hard blocks regardless of word count. I need to create a separate set for labels that should never start a title, even when combined with other words, and then update the blocking logic to check against this set first.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3784,"cache_read_input_tokens":75173,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3784},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b923ba25-2e78-4197-a1e6-b3c152deb8d9","uuid":"34446492-e760-41a1-a0b3-a60e4a1d908b"}
